  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Aircraft Technician (Airframe / Engine)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>In charge of inspecting and examining aircraft components for leaks, cracks, breaks, or other issues.</li><li>In charge of reading and utilizing maintenance manuals, illustrated parts catalogues, service bulletins, and other maintenance documents to troubleshoot and complete work assignments.</li><li>In charge of maintaining, repairing, and rebuilding aircraft structures, functional components, and parts such as wings and fuselage, rigging, hydraulic units, oxygen systems, fuel systems, gaskets, and seals.</li><li>Responsible in performing routine maintenance operations, such as the replacement of equipment and aircraft components.</li><li>Responsible in interpreting specifications or diagrams to inform installation, development or operation activities.</li><li>In charge of performing regular inspections to check for cracks, oil leaks, burned areas, foreign object damage, warping, distortions, missing segments, and wear</li><li>In charge of completing all tasks in the allotted time frame and to the quality standards of our company</li><li>Responsible in promoting safety within the workplace by monitoring others and yourself to guarantee all tasks are performed within the safety manual guidelines, and communicate with other mechanics and supervisors to coordinate repairs and keep apprised of safety concerns</li><li>Taking charge of the order supplies, equipment, materials, and parts for repairs and general maintenance</li><li>Taking charge of keeping detailed records of the inspections performed, repairs finished, maintenance procedures and ordered parts.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Min Nitec in Aerospace Engineering or related</li><li>Min 5 years of working experience in Aerospace Base Maintenance</li></ul><p>To submit your application, please apply online to <a href=\"mailto:apply@rn-care.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>apply@rn-care.com </strong></a>or call <strong>+(65) </strong><a href=\"tel:6513 5697\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\"><strong>6513 5697</strong></a> for private and confidential discussion.</p><p>Your interest will be treated with the strictest of confidence. We regret that only shortlisted candidates will be notified or contacted.</p><p><strong>RN Care Pte. Ltd</strong><br /><strong>EA License No: 17C8900</strong></p>",
